# {{zh-div|聲}} {{lb|zh|Chinese phonetics}} [[rising]] [[tone]] in [[Chinese]] [[phonetics]]

=====Usage notes=====
Historically, all of the four characters in {{l|zh|平上去入|tr=-|t=four tones of Middle Chinese}} are [[autology|autologies]]. Due to phonological changes over history, most of the characters historically pronounced with rising tone and voiced initials ({{l|zh|陽上}}) are pronounced with departing tone ({{l|zh|去聲}}) in most modern dialects, e.g. Mandarin (see {{pedia|濁上變去|lang=zh}}), including the character {{ltc-l|上}} itself. Therefore, this pronunciation was created to make it remain autological.

The tone {{l|zh|陽上}} is still conserved in some dialects, including Cantonese, Quanzhou Hokkien and Teochew.

